<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 07 at 7:05PM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Strong winds will impact portions of Charlotte and central
Halifax Counties through 730 PM EST...
At 705 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking showers with strong winds
along a line extending from Cullen to near Ridgeway. Movement was
east at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
South Boston...
Halifax...
Keysville...
Charlotte Court House...
Phenix...
Redoak...
and Clover.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways. Drivers are urged to slow down and use
extra caution to avoid hydroplaning.</instruction>
